# Label: H1, Preamble:#RTE

## Description

Real Time Events Report.
Maintenance Related FDE/STATUS Messages for Flight Crew Notice/Action. 
BOEING Airplane Health Monitoring. 

## Examples

### Example 1

```
RTE 1 13MAR26 1015 BAG-YMMF BAW9VA EGKK/TLPL 311B-BCG-00W-19 L 0955 13MAR26
FDE 21401145 A 1012 13MAR26
MSG 2112021 L 1013 13MAR26 CL M PL
DB ECSMC (LEFT)
FDE 34310332 A 0955 13MAR26
MSG 3457425 A 0955 13MAR26 ES H PL
DB AUTOPILOT FLIGHT DIRECTOR COMPUTER (CENTER)
DB AUTOPILOT FLIGHT DIRECTOR COMPUTER (LEFT)
DB AUTOPILOT FLIGHT DIRECTOR COMPUTER (RIGHT)
EOR
```

## Acronyms / Codes

```
- NCMM = Non-Correlated Maintenance Message
```

## Analysis

### Analysis for Example 1

```
- RTE = Real Time Events Report
- 1 = Leg Number
- 13MAR26 = DDMMMYY Leg Date
- 1015 = HHMM Leg Time
- BAG-YMMF = BA (Operator Code) / G-YMMF (A/C Registration)
- BAW9VA = Flight Number
- EGKK/TLPL = Departure Airport/Destination Airport
- 311B-BCG-00W-19 L = Central Maintenance Computer (CMC) or Part Number, Left (L) System
- 0955 = HHMM Real Time Event Timestamp
- 13MAR26 =  DDMMMYY Real Time Event Datestamp
- FDE = Flight Deck Effect
- 21401145 = Fault Code 214 011 45
- A = ACTIVE Fault
- 1012 = HHMM FDE Time Stamp
- MSG = Maintenance Message
- 2112021 = 21-12021 Maintenance Message ATA Number
- L = LATCHED Fault
- 1013 = HHMM MSG Time Stamp
- 13MAR26 = DDMMMYY FDE Time Stamp
- CL = CLIMB, Flight Phase
- M = Medium Priority Level
- PL = Unknown
- DB = Detected By (ECSMC = Environmental Control System Management Controller), Left
- EOR = End Of Report
```
